  "texts": [
    "That is, they are programmed to follow rules, of which at least some are of the form foot_1:",
    "The second feature -that moral sensitivity is a practical skill -offers a more positive characterisation of the notion.",
    "Such a characterisation is difficult, since it is of the nature of practical skills that they resist theoretical description.",
    "The capacity may best be characterised by example (Nussbaum, 1992 believes that it is best brought out by literary works), or by analogy with other uncodified skills.",
    "For instance, Nussbaum compares moral sensitivity to improvisational theatre or playing jazz music (Nussbaum, 1992, p. 74) and Hampshire compares it to the skill of translating texts (Hampshire, 1978, pp. 31-33)."
  ],
